{"title": "Missing Secure option in cookie configuration", "summary": "  A cookie that is configured to be secure ensures that a client will only send the cookie to the server when HTTPS is being used. This prevents the cookie from being observed by unauthorized third parties. ", "description": "\n\nA cookie that is configured to be secure ensures that a client will only send the cookie to the server when HTTPS is being used.\nThis prevents the cookie from being observed by unauthorized third parties.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u2705 Set `secure` values to `true` to force cookies to only send over HTTPS.\n  ```javascript\n    cookie({{ secure: true }})\n  ```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-614"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_express_insecure_cookie", "https://expressjs.com/en/advanced/best-practice-security.html#use-cookies-securely"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}